<br />

<br />
The melee method would work best if you can get the mermaids single. To get there just zone in take first right tunnel then hug left till on land, might need to fade to evoid a possible bulthar agro. Then check if the named is up in the castle, if not invis through, if so target her with eye of zomm or lull moving or bind sight song commonly used for track then lull her and invis through real fast. From inside castle you can go left or right, i always went left but thats just me. Then go across one of the bridges follow paths down avoid the water till your ready and get in and kill stuff. If you manage to single one just melee / mez till its dead. Song line up should be marr, snare, slow, haste, invis, saryns (hopefully you have VotS from ssra), mez, and finally either lull or HoS, depending on your mana pool / Fade pulling abilities. You can always lull pull mez and mem hos /shrug. 
<br />

<br />
As a time flagged bard with 4.5k hps these mobs aren't to be taken lightly, I died many times here with the charm method <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />Other than that its not to hard once you get used to it.
<br />

<br />
Melodico Harmonico 
<br />
65th bard Quellious
<br />
Vis Maior</span></td>
